**[1853, 03-22] Ms.A.8.1.1**

WP to Lysander Spooner

On Constitution and Horace Mann. Thinks together they can influence
politicians. “Whether I agree with [Spooner’s argument about the
Constitution] or not, I hold it to be a capital means of agitation.
Besides these men [politicians like Mann] owe you a public
acknowledgement of their conversion & consistency will strengthen them
with the public.”


